#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:331
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:364
msgid "EXAMPLE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:98
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{The bosses decide they will compete in the production of spicy "
"watermelon-flavoured toilet paper. Boss X asserts that \"Hot bottom roots\" "
"will be successful as their product is sustainable, because it embeds "
"watermelon seeds in the paper. Boss Y defends that the patented idea of "
"having triangular shaped paper will crush the competition, making \"Rusty "
"nachos\" the most used toilet paper worldwide.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:102
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:54
msgid "VICTORY CONDITIONS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:106
msgid ""
"Whoever achieves the \\textbf{victory} conditions, \\textbf{at any moment}, "
"can declare victory, and end the game. It can happen for more than one "
"player at the same time. In this case, all these players win the game."
msgstr ""

