#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:123
msgid "WORKERS COLLECTIVE VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:132
msgid ""
"\\textbf{All the workers win collectively} when they manage to achieve full "
"automation, meaning they manage to \\textbf{expropriate as many robots as "
"the number of workers}.  For games with at least 6 \\faPeopleGroup, when a "
"Luddite role is present, the robots destroyed by the Luddite also count "
"towards the workers' collective victory.  After an epic victory, the players "
"are encouraged to collect all the metallic coins used for playing and use "
"them for making a donation to a workers' union or social movement. In the "
"real world! We mean, out of this game, give those pennies some real use!"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:134
msgid "STARTUPPERS' VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:142
msgid ""
"The worker with the \\textbf{Startupper} secret role can win with "
"\\textbf{workers' collective victory} conditions or \\textbf{individually} "
"with a \\textbf{Class Betrayal}: Accumulating \\textbf{as many coins as the "
"total number of players} (workers + 2 bosses). The Startupper "
"\\textbf{cannot} declare the individual victory \\textbf{while Stressed}. "
"Also, for reaching the needed amount of cash, the Startupper can "
"\\textbf{steal} all the coins from the \\textbf{Union Fund} card.  The "
"Startupper victory (the victory of the small-medium enterprise) means that a "
"worker earns a lot and opens a new business!"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:144
msgid "SCABS' VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:148
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{Scab} can win with \\textbf{workers' collective victory} "
"conditions or \\textbf{together with a boss}: when a boss declares victory, "
"the Scab also wins \\textbf{if has been working} (not striking!) "
"\\textbf{for that boss} in the same turn (regardless if the Scab is Stressed "
"or not)."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:150
msgid "LUDDITE'S VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:156
msgid ""
"[6–10 \\faPeopleGroup.] The \\textbf{Luddite} can win with \\textbf{workers' "
"collective victory} conditions (counting all the expropriated and the "
"destroyed robots) or \\textbf{individually}. The individual victory happens "
"for the Luddite as soon as \\textbf{3 robots get destroyed}. To understand "
"how robots can be destroyed by the Luddite, see what happens in a failed "
"strike during phase 2 \"Strike\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:158
msgid "EARLY ENDING OF THE GAME - MONOPOLY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:165
msgid ""
"\\textbf{If a boss is eliminated} from the game (i.e. cannot pay Rent, or "
"cannot buy a robot after a successful Acceleration Strike held by the "
"workers), a \\textbf{Monopoly} is formed by the other boss. The workers "
"immediately and automatically expropriate the robots of the bankrupted "
"boss.  In a Monopoly situation, the winner gets determined based on the "
"\\textbf{number of robots controlled by the workers}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:172
msgid ""
"If the workers have at least as many robots (expropriated or destroyed by "
"the Luddite) as half of the number of workers (rounded up), they "
"collectively win (i.e. 3 workers with 2 robots, 4 workers with 2 robots...);"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:172
msgid "Otherwise, the surviving boss wins."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:174
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:91
msgid "GAMEPLAY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:179
msgid ""
"The game is played in rounds until 1 or more players achieve their victory "
"conditions.  When this happens, the game immediately ends.  A round consists "
"of \\textbf{6 phases}. Each phase is played a little differently; there is "
"no player turn order, and the actions of bosses or workers can take will "
"differ."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 1 HIRING}: bosses compete for workers by offering Contracts; "
"and may acquire robots to bolster production. Workers must choose a "
"Contract.  Players can discuss openly and negotiate."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 2 STRIKE}: bosses may compete for the Security Guard. Each "
"worker must decide to work or to strike. Players can discuss intentions, but "
"must decide and then reveal their actual action during a simultaneous vote."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 3 PRODUCTION}: bosses gain coins from the Bank, equal to the "
"production or their workers and robots."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid "\\textbf{Phase 4 PAYDAY}: bosses may pay their workers' salaries."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid "\\textbf{Phase 5 RENT}: both bosses and workers pay their Rent."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:194
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 6 UNION FUND}: workers may place their coins into the shared "
"Union Fund."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:198
msgid "Phase 1 HIRING"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:200
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:249
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:377
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:403
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:468
msgid "BOSSES ACTIONS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:213
msgid ""
"\\textbf{May acquire} as many \\textbf{robots} as they are able to; return 6 "
"\\faRubleSign\\ coins to the Bank (the pile of no one's coins) and place 1 "
"robot in front of them, blue side face up."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:213
msgid ""
"Must outline their \\textbf{Contract offers} - in return for work, how many "
"coins will Workers receive. Contracts are \\textbf{not binding}. Contracts "
"can be verbal or written, the role playing is up to you."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:213
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Holidays}: in addition to a salary, Contracts may include Holidays. "
"This does not have an extra cost for the boss. During phase 4 Payday, "
"Holidays allow workers to \\textbf{eliminate Stress}. To understand how "
"workers can get Stressed, see phase 5 Rent."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:215
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:256
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:385
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:414
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:474
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:539
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:131
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:199
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:259
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:312
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:342
msgid "WORKERS ACTIONS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:225
msgid "May attempt to negotiate with the bosses for better pay."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:225
msgid ""
"Must \\textbf{pick who they will work for} by giving a boss their personal "
"token."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:225
msgid ""
"Depending on the number of players, at most [5–6 \\faPeopleGroup] one, or [7–"
"8 \\faPeopleGroup] two, or [9–10 \\faPeopleGroup] three workers may "
"\\textbf{alternatively perform Public Work}, by placing their personal token "
"on the Public Work card."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:225
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Public Work} provides some workers (max. 1, 2, or 3 depending on "
"the number of players), with a Contract for a \\textbf{single round}, paying "
"\\textbf{1 coin} with \\textbf{included Holidays}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:227
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:319
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:392
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:427
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:489
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:138
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:208
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:273
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:323
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:349
msgid "ADDITIONAL DETAILS AND EXAMPLES"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:233
msgid ""
"Contracts given to workers can pay 0, up to anything a boss determines.  "
"Contracts can include promises of future pay increases. Contracts given to "
"individual workers can differ. Role playing/creativity when giving out "
"Contracts is encouraged!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:243
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{Boss X offers one Contract for 2 \\faRubleSign\\ and one "
"internship Contract starting from 0 and increasing by 1 coin each round. "
"Boss Y returns 6 \\faRubleSign\\ to the Bank to purchase 1 robot. And offers "
"three Contracts for 1 coin. Diana, the Luddite, rushes to take the only 2-"
"coins Contract, giving her personal token to boss X. Caino, the Startupper, "
"takes the Public Work, placing his player token on the Public Work card. As "
"there are 6 players (2 bosses + 4 workers) there is only 1 Public Work job "
"available. Beata, the Scab, believes in meritocracy and trusts boss X, so "
"takes the internship Contract. Abele, the Prolet, takes one of the 1-coin "
"Contracts from boss Y.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:247
msgid "Phase 2 STRIKE"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:254
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Must bid for the Security Guard}, even if their bid is 0, "
"\\textbf{using fingers} to indicate a number from 0 to 5 \\textbf{during the "
"simultaneous voting}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:261
msgid ""
"\\textbf{All non-Stressed workers} must decide to strike or work; using, "
"\\textbf{during the simultaneous voting}, a \\textbf{closed fist to strike "
"or an open hand to work}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:263
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:480
msgid "ALL PLAYERS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:268
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Simultaneous voting}: all the bosses and the non-Stressed workers "
"place their hands in the centre of the table, then \\textbf{simultaneously "
"reveal their action}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:270
msgid "VOTE RESOLUTION"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"First thing after the vote, \\textbf{both bosses pay} to the Bank an amount "
"of coins equal to \\textbf{their bid multiplied by the number of robots} "
"each of them controls.  For example: if a boss has 2 robots and indicated "
"the number 3 with the fingers, will have to pay 6 to the Bank. If the boss "
"has no robots, they will simply pay the bid amount, like if she had 1 robot."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"The winner of the bidding is the boss with the \\textbf{highest bid}: the "
"one who indicated the highest number \\textbf{with the fingers}, regardless "
"the actually paid amount."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Security Guard card}: then, the boss who won the bidding, receives "
"the Security Guard card for this round. This \\textbf{protects} this boss "
"from \\textbf{Expropriation Strike and Sabotage}. It does not protect "
"against Acceleration Strike."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"If both bosses bid the same amount with the fingers, neither receives the "
"Security Guard, yet both have to pay."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"For a \\textbf{strike to be successful}, the \\textbf{majority of workers} "
"must take the \\textbf{strike action} (e.g. with 4 workers, 3 workers must "
"strike). In case of tie (i.e. 2 out of 4 workers striking) or when just a "
"minority strikes, the strike fails. For calculating the required majority, "
"also the Stressed workers are considered (e.g. with 4 workers in total, if 2 "
"are Stressed it is impossible to reach the majority, as the Stressed ones "
"cannot strike)."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Failed Strike}: [5 \\faPeopleGroup] In absence of the Luddite role, "
"nothing happens, simply the striking workers will not produce during phase 3 "
"Production. [6–10 \\faPeopleGroup] The \\textbf{Luddite could attack}! If at "
"least two workers participated in a failed strike (which did not reach the "
"majority) and there is at least one robot in the game (either associated to "
"a worker or owned by a boss but not protected by the Security Guard card), "
"the bosses close their eyes and both count down aloud from 10. At this "
"moment, if the Luddite was one of the participants of the failed strike, "
"\\textbf{may destroy one robot} (either assigned to a worker or owned by a "
"boss, unless the Security Guard is protecting it). The Luddite can take the "
"robot card and put it in a robots' rubbish pile (any place on the table, "
"just make clear that this robot is not assigned to any player). The "
"destroyed robots won't produce coins for anyone, but will count towards the "
"workers' collective victory condition together with the expropriated robots. "
"Also, destroying robots helps the Luddite to achieve an individual victory: "
"If 3 robots get destroyed (over 3 failed strikes), see Luddite's victory "
"conditions."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"If a \\textbf{strike} is \\textbf{successful}; workers involved must "
"collectively \\textbf{decide} to \\textbf{Expropriate} a robot or "
"\\textbf{Accelerate} the acquisition of a robot. If the workers cannot agree "
"on what type of strike they want to carry out, then the bosses decide."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Expropriation strike}: workers \\textbf{take a single blue robot "
"owned by a boss} (excluding the boss whose robots are protected by the "
"Security Guard), flip the card to the red side and \\textbf{assign it to a "
"single worker}. If the workers cannot agree on who keeps the robot, the "
"bosses choose which worker will receive it."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:317
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Acceleration strike}: forcing a single \\textbf{boss to purchase a "
"blue robot} instantly, paying its cost immediately (6 \\faRubleSign). This "
"robot remains in control of the boss."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:329
msgid "\\textbf{Stressed workers cannot strike} and so must work."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:329
msgid ""
"The non-Stressed workers who took the Public Work, if any, can strike but "
"would receive neither the related 1-coin salary nor the free Holidays."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:329
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Workers who strike will not produce} during phase 3 Production for "
"their boss, regardless if the strike was successful or not."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:329
msgid ""
"At the end of this phase, return the Security Guard card to the centre of "
"the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:331
msgid "EXAMPLE: Security Guard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:344
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{During the simultaneous voting, boss Y bids 1 with one finger, "
"supposing that it will be enough for protecting their shiny new robot. But "
"boss X, evil in nature, also bids 1, even without having any robot to "
"protect! As they both bid the same, nobody gets the Security Guard and boss "
"Y's shiny robot is unprotected, exactly what boss X was hoping for. Even if "
"nobody got the Security Guard, both bosses have to pay.  Boss Y pays their "
"bid of 1 multiplied by 1 (1 robot): for a total of 1. This mastermind move "
"will not be free for boss X: They control no robots but must still pay their "
"bid of 1.\\newline ... in a later round, boss X has 1 robot and bids 3, "
"while boss Y has 2 robots and bids 2. In this case, boss X pays 3 to the "
"Bank, boss Y pays 4 (2 multiplied by 2 robots).  Boss X is protected by the "
"Security Guard (Boss X bid higher, despite boss Y paying more).}"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:346
msgid "EXAMPLE: Strike"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:356
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{At the same time of the bosses' bidding, the workers' vote "
"happens. Abele, Caino, and Diana, in an optimism surge, close their fists to "
"indicate that they are striking, while Beata keeps it open and goes to work. "
"With 3 participants, the majority of the workers' is secured and the strike "
"is successful. At this point, Abele, Caino and Diana can decide to "
"Accelerate (force one boss to buy a robot immediately) or to Expropriate one "
"of the robots a boss already owns. They decide to take one of the robots "
"from boss Y, that are not protected by the Security Guard. Caino the "
"Startupper asks Abele and Diana if he can keep the robot, they have nothing "
"against this and they accept.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:358
msgid "EXAMPLE: Sabotage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:371
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{[6–10 \\faPeopleGroup: the Luddite role is present] ... the next "
"round, boss X has 1 robot and again manages to get the Security Guard, and "
"boss Y also has 1 robot. At the same time as the bosses' bidding, the "
"workers reveal their votes: Abele the Prolet and Diana the Luddite close "
"their hands in a fist (they strike), while Beata keeps her hand open (she "
"works). Caino has to go to work, as he got Stressed in the previous round "
"(he couldn't pay the Rent in phase 5). So, only two workers over four are "
"striking, not reaching the majority needed for proceeding to a strike. Even "
"if the strike failed, the Luddite (a secret role for games with at least 6 "
"\\faPeopleGroup) can still do things! The bosses close their eyes and, "
"aloud, count back from ten. In a rage, Diana the Luddite destroys boss Y's "
"robot and swiftly moves boss Y's blue robot card to the centre of the table. "
"Now the workers are one robot closer to the workers' collective victory, but "
"the Luddite is also closer to an individual victory!}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:375
msgid "Phase 3 PRODUCTION"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:383
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{robot and non-striking worker produces 5 \\faRubleSign}\\ for "
"their boss. Each boss gains coins from the Bank equal to the total "
"production of their workers and robots."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:390
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{expropriated robot produces 1} coin for the worker it is "
"assigned to; gain coins from the Bank equal to total production."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:398
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{Boss X has 1 robot producing 5 and a Contract with Beata who also "
"produces 5.  Abele and Diana went on strike, so they don't produce. Caino's "
"robot produces 1.  Boss X gains 10 \\faRubleSign; boss Y gains no coins; and "
"Caino gains 1 coin.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:401
msgid "Phase 4 PAYDAY"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:412
msgid ""
"Decide on \\textbf{whether or not to pay their workers} as promised in the "
"Contracts given. Each boss can decide whether to distribute the salary as "
"promised, keep it with an excuse, pay it only in part, or keep promises with "
"some worker/s and not with others. Most likely, whoever went on strike will "
"not receive any salary. Also, if an offered Contract includes Holidays, the "
"boss may remove the worker's Stress for free (Untap the character card)."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:425
msgid ""
"Each worker who took the \\textbf{Public Work} (if any) and did not strike, "
"earns \\textbf{1 coin} and receive \\textbf{free Holidays}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:425
msgid ""
"Also, each Stressed worker can \\textbf{pay for their own Holidays} by "
"giving \\textbf{2 \\faRubleSign}\\ to the Bank. They may take this from "
"their own money and/or from the Union Fund card (see phase 6 Union Fund)."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:425
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Holidays} allow workers to \\textbf{remove their Stress}. To "
"understand how workers can get Stressed, see phase 5 Rent. To remove the "
"Stress, \\textbf{Untap the character card}, placing it straight in front of "
"the player."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:441
msgid ""
"The \\textbf{Mayor} is a \\textbf{prize lasting one round}. Initially, it is "
"placed at the centre of the table, not assigned to any boss/worker. It goes "
"to the boss who \\textbf{has at least one working} (non-striking) "
"\\textbf{worker}, \\textbf{respects all the Contracts} (excluding the "
"striking workers' Contracts), and \\textbf{pays at least 1 coin} to each "
"working worker. If only one boss respects these conditions, the Mayor card "
"goes to this boss, and will be very useful for dealing with the Rent in "
"phase 5. If no boss deserves it, and at least one worker worked (didn't "
"strike) for a boss (not for the Public Work), then one of the workers "
"becomes the new Mayor (workers decide whom). Otherwise, if both bosses "
"deserve it, or if no boss deserved it and no worker actually worked for any "
"boss (so no boss had the possibility to respect the Contracts), then nobody "
"gets the Mayor card."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:462
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{Caino was Stressed, and worked for the Public Work, so he gets "
"directly 1 coin and free Holidays, which means he is not Stressed any more "
"and Untaps his character card. Beata worked for boss X, and asks for her 1-"
"coin salary. But boss X had to gift to the firstborn a submarine trip for "
"seeing the Titanic, and cannot spend more this month, apologizes follow. "
"Abele and Diana, as they participated in a strike (even if a failed one) do "
"not receive any salary. Boss Y had only an employee, Abele, but he went on "
"strike, so boss Y cannot get the Mayor card (didn't have at least one "
"working worker). Boss X had a Contract with Beata and another with Diana. "
"Diana participated in a strike, so she is not relevant for deciding on the "
"Mayor card. Beata instead went to work, yet her salary has not been paid. If "
"her salary had been paid, boss X would have got the Mayor card. So, no boss "
"deserves to be the Mayor, and Beata actually worked for boss X. This means "
"that the Mayor card goes to a worker.  Everybody considers that Beata "
"deserves it, so she gets elected as the new Mayor!\\newline [...] the next "
"round, only Caino accepted to work for boss X with a 1-coin salary.  "
"Unexpectedly, boss X respected the Contract and paid him 1 coin. Boss Y was "
"hit by a mass strike instead, and didn't even have the option to pay the "
"workers. Thanks to the gained trust, boss X becomes the \"lesser evil\" and "
"gets elected as the new Mayor.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:466
msgid "Phase 5 RENT"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:472
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{boss} must \\textbf{pay} a Rent of \\textbf{2 \\faRubleSign}\\ "
"to the Bank."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:478
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{worker} must \\textbf{pay} a Rent of \\textbf{1 coin} to the "
"Bank."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:487
msgid ""
"The player, worker or boss, who has the \\textbf{Mayor card}, if any, can "
"indicate \\textbf{which players} (just one, some of them, or all) "
"\\textbf{will not pay} any Rent for this turn (herself/himself included). "
"Additionally, this player can also \\textbf{increase the Rent by 1 coin for "
"one player} for this turn."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid "\\textbf{If any worker cannot pay} the Rent:"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid ""
"They may use the coins on the \\textbf{Union Fund} card for paying the Rent;"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid ""
"If there are no coins on the Union Fund card, the workers who cannot pay "
"\\textbf{get Stressed}: these players Tap (rotate 90 degrees) their "
"character card. A Stressed worker cannot strike, so in phase 2 will have to "
"go to work."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid ""
"Any worker that has no coins and is already Stressed, just stays like that, "
"without paying the Rent."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid ""
"\\textbf{If a boss cannot pay the Rent}, see \\textbf{Early ending of the "
"game - Monopoly}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:505
msgid ""
"At the end of this phase, return the Mayor card to the centre of the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:533
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{As the new Mayor, the first law issued by boss X is to close down "
"the fine arts museum in order to limit public spending. The second law, "
"assigned the same museum to be the new house of the Mayor. With an act of "
"charity, boss X allows Caino, the most loyal of the workers, to be the "
"housekeeper. So, neither boss X nor Caino will have to pay the Rent for this "
"round. Additionally, the new Mayor declares a central street to be a new "
"space for freedom of expression, allowing any kind of street artist to "
"perform there, day and night. Obviously, the residents will have to "
"contribute with the initiative, like paying the paint for the graffiti "
"artists. Fortuitously, that's where boss Y resides, so boss Y's Rent will be "
"raised to 3 \\faRubleSign\\ for this round.\\newline [...] the next round, "
"Diana had some savings, and even after participating in two strikes can "
"still pay her Rent to the Bank. Abele and Beata, instead, cannot pay the "
"Rent. Luckily, there are some shared savings on the Union Fund card (see "
"phase 6): 1 coin. This is enough for paying one Rent. Beata the Scab doesn't "
"mind getting Stressed, so Abele takes that coin, and pays the Rent. Beata "
"Taps the character card (rotating it by 90 degrees), and will not be able to "
"participate in any strike until she manages to recover from the Stress. "
"Caino was the only one to get a salary in this round, so now he can pay 1 "
"coin of Rent. Boss X pays 2 \\faRubleSign, complaining about the increasing "
"expenses for the air conditioning of his golf course. Instead, boss Y is "
"completely out of coins and, desperate, declares the end of the \"Rusty "
"nachos\" dream while boss X celebrates the new Monopoly situation.  This "
"triggers an Early ending of the game - Monopoly. At this point, what matters "
"is the number of robots controlled or destroyed by workers. Sadly, in boss "
"Y's abandoned factory, there isn't even a robot to steal. So, now workers "
"have 1 expropriated robot, and 1 destroyed robot: a total of 2 robots, that "
"reaches half of the workers' number! All the workers win collectively, and "
"celebrate playing boardgames while their robots cultivate and cook the "
"dinner.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:537
msgid "Phase 6 UNION FUND"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:544
msgid ""
"Freely, each worker may now make new donations to the Union Fund. The coins "
"on this card will help workers to pay the Rent in phase 5."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:546
msgid "ADDITIONAL DETAILS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:551
msgid ""
"Note that the worker with the Startupper secret role may steal this money "
"for winning the game at any moment!"
msgstr ""

#. type: textbf{#1}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:554
msgid ""
"At this point, the game continues with phase 1 and follows all the phases "
"again."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:556
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:372
msgid "ADDITIONAL RULES"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid "Bosses can lend coins to each other."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid "Bosses can bribe the Luddite to destroy a robot of their choice!"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid "Bosses can keep their coins secret, or reveal all or part of it."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid "Workers cannot keep their coins hidden."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid ""
"The coins of the Union Fund have to be kept in sight on the Union Fund card."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid "Workers can openly discuss about strikes."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/five_to_ten_players.en.tex:567
msgid ""
"In case of disagreement between workers (e.g. who should take an "
"expropriated robot), bosses will decide."
msgstr ""

#. type: chapter{#2}
#: The_Fully_Automated_Board_Game.en.tex:113
msgid "Rules for 2 to 4 players"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:9
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Beware!} The rules of the 2–4 \\faPeopleGroup\\ game are very "
"different from the ones for 5–10 \\faPeopleGroup! \\textbf{Some cards have a "
"text saying \"2–4 \\faPeopleGroup\"}: the rules here are for games from 2 to "
"4 players. For games with 5–10 \\faPeopleGroup, go to page "
"\\pageref{ch:5-10}."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Take a \\textbf{boss card} and place it at the centre of the table. It is "
"\\textbf{automated}, it is therefore \\textbf{not a player}."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Give \\textbf{each player a Prolet worker card} (red flag symbol, without "
"any secret role) face up. They place it in front of them on the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Give a \\textbf{personal token} to each player. Try to find the best suited "
"token for each person, so that the association will be easier to remember. "
"Keep aside the hourglass token."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid "Place the \\textbf{robot cards deck} at the centre of the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Remove the \"Depression\" Contracts card from the game. Or keep it in case "
"you want to play a harder game. Place the deck of \\textbf{Contracts cards} "
"face down at the centre of the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Place the deck of \\textbf{Event cards} face down at the centre of the "
"table. Assemble the Event cards deck with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid "\\textbf{2 players}: 8 random Event cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid "\\textbf{3 players}: 10 random Event cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid "\\textbf{4 players}: all 17 Event cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Place the \\textbf{6 phase cards} (on the \"2–4 \\faPeopleGroup\" side) face "
"up, one next to the other, at the centre of the table. Place the "
"\\textbf{phase marker token} (the one with an hourglass drawing) on the "
"first phase card."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"Create a space for the \\textbf{Bank} where you put a \\textbf{pile of "
"coins}. Take plenty of coins, the exact amount is not important (for a 3 "
"\\faPeopleGroup\\ game, you will need approximately 30 coins, representing "
"30 \\faRubleSign). Use some real coins, if you have them, for representing "
"the \\faRubleSign, the in-game currency. If you don't have coins at hand, "
"you can use anything you \"borrowed\" from work or any other small and "
"homogeneous object you can find. Alternatively, note the amounts on a piece "
"of paper."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"All the workers and the automated boss start with \\textbf{0 \\faRubleSign\\ "
"coins each}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:58
msgid ""
"Whoever achieves the victory conditions, at any moment, can declare victory, "
"and end the game. It can happen for more than one player at the same time. "
"In this case, all these players win the game."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:60
msgid "COLLECTIVE VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:63
msgid ""
"All players still in the game, win when they \\textbf{control as many robots "
"as there are players}, eliminated or not."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:68
msgid ""
"After an epic victory, the players are encouraged to collect all the "
"metallic coins used for playing and use them for making a donation to a "
"workers' union or social movement. In the real world! We mean, out of this "
"game, give those pennies some real use!"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:70
msgid "COLLECTIVE DEFEAT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:79
msgid "All the players lose the game when:"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:79
msgid ""
"\\textbf{The automated boss has as many robots as all the players}, "
"eliminated and still in play;"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:79
msgid ""
"A player should draw an Event card, but the \\textbf{Events deck ran out of "
"cards};"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:79
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Half of the players are eliminated} (when playing in 3, this "
"happens with the elimination of 2 \\faPeopleGroup)."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:81
msgid "CLASS BETRAYAL VICTORY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:87
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Any non-Stressed player with 8 \\faRubleSign\\ coins}, or two non-"
"Stressed players united by the Marriage Event card with 10 \\faRubleSign, "
"can declare themselves the winner(s) as class traitor(s)! If more than one "
"player fulfils the Class Betrayal victory conditions at the same time, they "
"can all declare victory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:95
msgid ""
"The game is played in rounds until 1 or more players achieve the Class "
"Betrayal victory conditions or the workers' collective victory or collective "
"defeat conditions are met. When this happens, the game immediately ends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:98
msgid ""
"A round consists of 6 phases. The starting player changes every round and is "
"in charge of revealing one Event and one Contracts card. Each phase is "
"played differently."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:101
msgid ""
"The \\textbf{first starting player} is the one who most recently "
"participated in a protest or strike (in real life or in the game)."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 1 State-funded innovation}: the boss could buy a "
"\\textbf{robot}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 2 Event}: the starting player reveals an \\textbf{Event} card "
"and applies its effect."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 3 Contracts}: the starting player reveals a "
"\\textbf{Contracts} card, and picks a Contract first. Clockwise, the other "
"players choose between the remaining Contracts."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 4 Strike}: simultaneously, non-Stressed workers reveal "
"whether they will \\textbf{strike or work}. Players \\textbf{cannot discuss} "
"strike intentions."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 5 Payday}: players who worked get a \\textbf{salary}. Robots "
"\\textbf{produce}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:114
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Phase 6 Rent}: the players pay the \\textbf{Rent} to the automated "
"boss. The player on the left of the starting player is the new starting "
"player."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:118
msgid "Phase 1 STATE-FUNDED INNOVATION"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:120
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:306
msgid "AUTOMATED BOSS ACTIONS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:125
msgid ""
"If the automated \\textbf{boss has at least 15 \\faRubleSign}, move 15 "
"\\faRubleSign\\ to the Bank, and place next to the boss card a \\textbf{new "
"robot} card on the blue side."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:129
msgid "Phase 2 EVENT"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:136
msgid ""
"The starting player must reveal an \\textbf{Event card and apply} its "
"effect. If there is no card left to pick, see collective defeat."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:140
msgid "SYMBOLS ON THE EVENT CARDS"
msgstr ""

#. type: textbf{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:147
msgid "PLAY AND DISCARD"
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:155
msgid "\\textbf{PERMANENT EFFECT}, the affected player keeps the card"
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:163
msgid "This card affects the \\textbf{CURRENT STARTING PLAYER}"
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:171
msgid "This card affects a \\textbf{CHOSEN PLAYER}"
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:179
msgid "This card affects \\textbf{MORE THAN ONE PLAYER}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:182
msgid ""
"If the unavoidable and immediate effect of an Event card is to eliminate a "
"player, ignore this effect: \\textbf{Event cards cannot directly eliminate "
"players}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:193
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{The automated boss has no coins at the beginning of the game, so "
"clearly will not buy a robot just yet. Between the 3 workers, Asdrubale, "
"Bedelia and Candida, the last participating in a protest was Bedelia (the "
"management of the data centre where she works is blocking the negotiation of "
"the collective agreement, so she plugged a bunch of short network cables to "
"adjacent ethernet ports of many switches), so she starts the game revealing "
"the first Event card: the \"Gambling\" card says \"one of the players with "
"most coins gives all but 1 coin to the boss\", but none of the 3 "
"\\faPeopleGroup\\ have any coins, and the card is discarded (and no one gets "
"Stressed).}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:197
msgid "Phase 3 CONTRACTS"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:206
msgid ""
"The starting player must reveal a \\textbf{Contracts card}, choose a "
"Contract and \\textbf{place the personal token} on it. The other players, in "
"clockwise order, must choose between the remaining Contracts listed on the "
"card, placing their personal token on the chosen Contract."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:222
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Get Stressed}: Contracts may cause Stress, this will be applied "
"during phase 5 Payday."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:222
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Holidays included}: in addition to the salary, Contracts may "
"include Holidays.  Holidays will allow players to eliminate Stress during "
"phase 5 Payday."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:222
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Permanent Contract}: will last for more rounds, until the player "
"accepts another Contract or participates in a strike. This player will keep "
"this card next to the character card during the Contract's validity."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:222
msgid ""
"A \\textbf{Contracts card cannot directly eliminate a player}: if a Contract "
"says \"get Stressed\" but you are already Stressed, you are unaffected."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:222
msgid ""
"When the Contracts cards run out, shuffle the discarded Contracts cards "
"(except the permanent Contract cards still in use by the players)."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubsection{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:224
msgid "SYMBOLS ON THE CONTRACTS CARDS"
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:233
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Get Stressed}: Contracts may cause Stress, this will be applied "
"during phase 5."
msgstr ""

#. type: minipage
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:242
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Holidays included}: in addition to the salary, Contracts may "
"include Holidays.  Holidays will allow players to eliminate Stress during "
"phase 5."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:253
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{Since it's her turn to start, Bedelia draws a Contracts card, and "
"shows it to everyone. It's the \"Boom\" card! She chooses the \"3-coins "
"Contract (with Stress)\" first. On her left, Candida, picks the \"2-coins "
"Contract\" from the remaining Contracts. Finally, Asdrubale takes the \"1-"
"coin permanent Contract (until strike)\". Asdrubale then places the "
"Contracts card next to his Prolet character card, keeping it until he "
"decides to rescind the Contract. On the card, there is a fourth Contract "
"that no one will take, as there are only 3 players.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:257
msgid "Phase 4 STRIKE"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:270
msgid ""
"All the non-eliminated \\textbf{non-Stressed} players place one hand towards "
"the centre of the table and, \\textbf{at the same time, must vote} one of "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:270
msgid "\\textbf{thumb up} = strike for \\textbf{Acceleration}"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:270
msgid "\\textbf{closed fist} = strike for \\textbf{Expropriation}"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:270
msgid "\\textbf{open hand} = \\textbf{work}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:270
msgid "Alternatively, they can write their action on a piece of paper."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:289
msgid "\\textbf{Stressed players cannot strike} and so must work."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:289
msgid ""
"\\textbf{It's forbidden to talk} or communicate \\textbf{about strikes}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:289
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Acceleration Strike: every thumb raised creates one robot for the "
"boss}.  The boss loses all the coins earned up to that point. Beware that "
"\\textbf{more than one robot can appear in the same round}! For example, if "
"all the workers vote raising their thumbs, the boss loses all the savings "
"and immediately receives those many robots, triggering the collective defeat!"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:289
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Expropriation Strike}: If the \\textbf{majority} of players (with 2 "
"\\faPeopleGroup\\ the majority is 2; with 3 \\faPeopleGroup\\ majority is 2; "
"with 4 \\faPeopleGroup\\ majority is 3) voted with a closed fist, "
"\\textbf{take one robot} from the boss, flip it to the red side and assign "
"it to a single player.  You can also expropriate a robot created by an "
"Acceleration Strike in this very round. If the strike does not reach the "
"majority, nothing happens, but the striking players will not get any salary "
"in phase 5 Payday."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:300
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{After a short countdown, the 3 \\faPeopleGroup\\ express their "
"decisions with their hands: Bedelia wants to work (secretly intends to win "
"with a Class Betrayal) and so keeps her hand open; Candida also intends to "
"work, and therefore exposes her open hand; Asdrubale wasn't really "
"interested in the permanent Contract, and decided to do an Acceleration "
"Strike! He is showing his thumb up, which indicates the Acceleration Strike. "
"Consequently, he returns the permanent Contract card to the area of "
"discarded Contracts, and places a new blue robot next to the boss. The "
"automated boss discards all the owned coins, if any.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:304
msgid "Phase 5 PAYDAY"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:310
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{robot} the boss controls \\textbf{produces 2 \\faRubleSign}\\ "
"for the boss."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:321
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{non-striking worker} receives the \\textbf{salary} and applies "
"the \\textbf{additional effects} from the chosen Contract. The effect of "
"\"\\textbf{with Holidays}\" is to remove the Stress, Untapping the character "
"card. The effect of \"\\textbf{get Stressed}\" is to Tap the character card "
"(remember that a Stressed player cannot do any kind of strike)."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:321
msgid ""
"Each \\textbf{Expropriated robot} produces \\textbf{1 coin} for the worker "
"it is assigned to."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:329
msgid ""
"Players who attempt any kind of strike will receive neither the salary from "
"the chosen Contract, nor its positive or negative effect (i.e. \"get "
"Stressed\" or \"with Holidays\")."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:336
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{The new robot produces 2 \\faRubleSign\\ for the boss. Bedelia "
"receives 3 \\faRubleSign\\ from the Bank, but has to Tap her Prolet "
"character card, as the chosen Contract indicated that she would have become "
"Stressed. Candida receives 2 \\faRubleSign\\ from the Bank. Asdrubale went "
"on strike, so he receives nothing.}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:340
msgid "Phase 6 RENT"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:347
msgid ""
"Unless an Event card changes this, \\textbf{each worker pays 1 coin directly "
"to the boss}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:361
msgid ""
"A player who \\textbf{can't pay the Rent gets Stressed}. \\textbf{If already "
"Stressed} and cannot pay the Rent, this player is considered "
"\\textbf{eliminated} and stops participating in the game."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:361
msgid ""
"If a player needs to pay Rent of 2 \\faRubleSign\\ (e.g. due to the "
"\"Birth\" Event card), but has only 1 coin, they pay nothing but become "
"Stressed. If they are already Stressed, they are eliminated."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:361
msgid ""
"\\textbf{If half of the players are eliminated, the game is over}, see "
"collective de- feat. In a game with 3 \\faPeopleGroup, this happens when 2 "
"\\faPeopleGroup\\ are eliminated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:361
msgid ""
"The player on the left of the starting player is the new starting player. "
"The game continues with phase 1, and follows all the phases again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:368
msgid ""
"\\itsmall{Bedelia pays her 1-coin Rent, moving one of her 3 \\faRubleSign\\ "
"next to the boss card. Candida does the same thing. Asdrubale, having no "
"coins for paying the Rent, has to Tap his Prolet card (he is now Stressed).}"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid ""
"An elimination can happen only if a player cannot pay the Rent during phase "
"6 and is already Stressed."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid ""
"If some effect of an Event card cannot be applied, skip it and apply the "
"remaining effects on that card."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid ""
"It is forbidden to communicate about strikes: only the voting during phase 4 "
"will reveal the workers' actions."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid "Workers pay the Rent directly to the automated boss."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:385
msgid ""
"In case of disagreement between players (e.g. who should control an "
"expropriated robot), the starting player will decide."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:389
msgid "NOTES ON THE EVENT CARDS"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:393
msgid "Birth"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:396
msgid ""
"If a married couple (see Marriage card) has a Birth, they can decide who "
"takes care of the child in case there will be a Divorce Event."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:398
msgid "Collective Agreement"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:401
msgid ""
"Each Contract on this round's Contracts card can be chosen by more than one "
"player."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:403
msgid "Dentist"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:407
msgid ""
"If possible, one player should pay or get Stressed. If no player has 2 "
"\\faRubleSign, and all players are already Stressed, this card is the least "
"of your problems and you can ignore it."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:409
msgid "Divorce"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:412
msgid ""
"If the Marriage card is in game, both of the involved players lose all the "
"coins, and remove the Stress, if not, ignore this card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:414
msgid "Eviction"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:416
msgid ""
"The card effect is applied to the player who has the Gentrification card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:418
msgid "Gentrification"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:421
msgid ""
"Once one player has this card, the only way to get rid of it is that any "
"player draws the Eviction card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:423
msgid "Mandatory Overtime"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:427
msgid ""
"If the player who picked this card participates in a strike this round, they "
"do not get the 1 coin extra, and do not get Stressed due to this card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:429
msgid "Marriage"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:434
msgid ""
"You can bring the characters cards closer together and put this card in the "
"middle. Even if married, the Rent is 1 coin for each worker. What changes is "
"that one player may pay both Rents. Marriage modifies the Class Betrayal "
"winning conditions, check them out."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:436
msgid "Production Bonus"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:439
msgid ""
"If the player who picked this card participates in a strike this round, they "
"do not receive the extra 2 \\faRubleSign."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:441
msgid "Rotating Shifts"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:444
msgid ""
"Participants in a strike this round, do not get the 1 coin extra, and do not "
"get Stressed due to this card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:446
msgid "Sabotage"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:449
msgid ""
"If there is only a red robot (an expropriated one), destroy it, if there are "
"no robots in play, ignore this card."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph{#1}
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:451
msgid "Workers' Union"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/two_to_four_players.en.tex:453
msgid "If the boss is out of money, you are out of luck."
msgstr ""

#. type: chapter{#2}
#: The_Fully_Automated_Board_Game.en.tex:129
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:6
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Acceleration Strike (action)} A strike in which a boss is forced "
"to buy a robot immediately. This robot remains in control of the boss."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:9
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Bank (place)} The reservoir of coins, property of no player."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:13
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Boss (role/card)} The stingy blue character. [2–4 "
"\\faPeopleGroup] An automated role collecting the Rent, and buying robots. "
"[5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] Two human players."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:17
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Class Betrayal (winning condition)} [2–4 \\faPeopleGroup] Any "
"player can win individually by accumulating coins. [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] "
"The Startupper can win by accumulating coins."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:22
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Contract (card/agreement)} [2–4 \\faPeopleGroup] Each of the "
"enlistment options on the Contracts cards. [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] The "
"agreements between bosses and workers happening during phase 1."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:26
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Event (card)} [2–4 \\faPeopleGroup] During phase 2, the starting "
"player reveals an Event card that can affect this/any/all players in an "
"instantaneous or permanent fashion."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:30
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Expropriation Strike (action)} A strike in which workers can "
"take a robot from a chosen boss. [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] From a boss without "
"the Security Guard."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:35
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Holidays (action)} [2–4 \\faPeopleGroup] Workers can choose a "
"Contract with Holidays to remove Stress. [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] Workers can "
"remove Stress with Holidays if they: pay 2 \\faRubleSign; or choose the "
"Public Work; or get it as part of a Contract offered by a boss."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:40
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Luddite (role/card)} [6–10 \\faPeopleGroup] A saboteur secret "
"role for workers. Adds an individual winning option, destroying 3 robots "
"during failed strikes. Destroyed robots also count towards the workers' "
"collective victory."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:46
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Monopoly (winning condition)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] When a boss "
"gets eliminated due to not being able to pay the Rent or cannot buy a robot "
"after a successful Acceleration Strike. The winner gets determined based on "
"the expropriated or destroyed robots. See the victory conditions Early "
"ending of the game."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:50
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Prolet (role/card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] A “virtual pauper” "
"secret role for workers. Does not have any individual winning option. It's "
"very focused on striking!"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:55
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Public Work (card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] During phase 1, "
"workers can take this Contract instead of one offered from the bosses. There "
"is only one such job in games with 5–6 \\faPeopleGroup, two in games with 7–"
"8 \\faPeopleGroup, and 3 in games with 9–10 \\faPeopleGroup."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:59
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Rent (phase)} In the Rent phase, each player pays an amount of "
"coins. With [2–4 \\faPeopleGroup] the Rent goes to the automated boss, [5–10 "
"\\faPeopleGroup] The Rent goes to the Bank."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:63
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Sabotage (action)} [6–10 \\faPeopleGroup] In phase 2 Strike, the "
"Luddite player can destroy a robot during a failed strike."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:69
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Scab (role/card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] A workaholic secret "
"role for workers. Adds an individual winning option: each Scab can win "
"together with a victory-declaring boss (a boss winning either with coins "
"accumulation or Monopoly) if they were working (not on strike) for this boss "
"when the victory declaration happens."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:73
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Security Guard (card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] It is a protection "
"from Expropriation Strike and Sabotage. The bosses bid for getting it (from "
"0 to 5 fingers, check phase 2 rules)."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:78
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Startupper (role/card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] A petite "
"bourgeoisie secret role for workers.  Adds a Class Betrayal individual "
"winning option via the accumulation of coins and stealing from the Union "
"Fund."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:82
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Stress (status)} A condition for workers that hinders them from "
"striking, and thus forces them to work."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:86
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Tap/Untap (action)} Tap your character card, placing it rotated "
"90° in front of you for indicating Stress. Untap placing it straight."
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: contents_tex/glossary.en.tex:90
msgid ""
"\\paragraph{Union Fund (card)} [5–10 \\faPeopleGroup] The workers can share "
"their coins, placing them on this card during phase 6."
msgstr ""

